#!/usr/bin/env bash
# Pre-commit guard — blocks foreign edits to payload/sources/**/*.cs
# (the Revit / AutoCAD / Max / shared MCP brokers) unless the committing
# user explicitly opts in via ARCHHUB_ALLOW_CS_EDIT=1.
#
# Why: 2026-05-25 — Antigravity IDE (Google) made undiscussed
# destructive edits to AcadMCPApp.cs (broker port 48885→48887, breaks
# Python connector), RevitMCPCore.cs (NopFP failure-preprocessor), and
# ScriptCompiler.cs (NopFP user-code template inject). Source-controlled
# guard catches every future agent that touches these without an
# AgDR + founder sign-off.
#
# Opt-in path:
#   ARCHHUB_ALLOW_CS_EDIT=1 git commit ...
#
# Bypass path (emergency):
#   git commit --no-verify
#   (use only if hook itself is broken)

set -euo pipefail

# When the env flag is set, hook is a no-op. The user has explicitly
# approved the .cs edit (e.g. founder wrote it themselves or signed off
# on an AgDR that touches the broker).
if [[ "${ARCHHUB_ALLOW_CS_EDIT:-0}" == "1" ]]; then
    exit 0
fi

# Inspect the changes staged for this commit only — pre-commit runs
# before the commit object exists, so we diff index vs HEAD.
STAGED_CS=$(git diff --cached --name-only --diff-filter=ACMR \
            -- 'payload/sources/**/*.cs' 2>/dev/null || true)

if [[ -n "$STAGED_CS" ]]; then
    cat >&2 <<'EOF'
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  COMMIT BLOCKED — payload/sources/**/*.cs edit detected
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
EOF
    echo "" >&2
    echo "Staged broker source files:" >&2
    echo "$STAGED_CS" | sed 's/^/  /' >&2
    echo "" >&2
    cat >&2 <<'EOF'
These files control the Revit / AutoCAD / 3ds Max MCP brokers and the
shared script compiler. They were edited destructively by an agent on
2026-05-25 — port numbers changed, transaction wrappers bypassed.

Founder mandate (CLAUDE.md + AGENTS.md):
  - Broker .cs files require an AgDR before any edit
  - AgDR must record the port/protocol contract change + founder sign-off
  - Rebuild + redeploy + CDP-verify is part of the same iteration

If you are an autonomous agent: STOP. Open AGENTS.md at the repo root
and follow the mandate set there. Do not edit .cs files in
payload/sources/ unless you have written an AgDR and the founder has
signed off in chat.

If you are the founder (or have explicit sign-off):
  ARCHHUB_ALLOW_CS_EDIT=1 git commit -m "..."

To inspect what changed before deciding:
  git diff --cached -- payload/sources/**/*.cs
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
EOF
    exit 1
fi

exit 0
